      "value": "The literature survey will show: (1) pristine Si band gap: LDA ~0.5 eV, GGA ~0.6 eV, both far below experimental 1.17 eV; (2) for the Si vacancy, LDA often places the defect state near or inside the conduction band due to over-delocalization, while GGA (especially PBE) can produce a gap state — but neither is quantitatively reliable without GW corrections; (3) the hypothesis is qualitatively correct but oversimplified — the actual picture depends on charge state, supercell size, and whether finite-size corrections are applied."
